<h3 class="heading-size-5">JavaScript</h3>

<p>Call the <code>carousel()</code> function on your carousel selector:</p>

<pre><code>$('.carousel').carousel();</code></pre>

<p>The following options can be passed to the function to customize the carousels:</p>

<table class="table">
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Option</th>
            <th>Description</th>
            <th>Default</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td><code>nav</code></td>
            <td>Create next/previous buttons</td>
            <td><code>true</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>pagination</code></code></td>
            <td>Create pagination bullets</td>
            <td><code>true</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>owl</code></td>
            <td>Pass any custom <a href="http://owlcarousel2.github.io/OwlCarousel2/docs/api-options.html" target="blank">OwlCarousel options</a> to the carousel</td>
            <td><code>{}</code></td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<p>The above options can be passed to the function like so:</p>

<pre><code>$('.carousel').carousel({
    pagination: false,
    owl: {
        items: 6
    }
});</code></pre>

<p>Default carousels will now reflect these options:</p>

<pre><code class="html">&lt;div class="carousel">
